SELF_AWARENESS

DESCRIPTION


Self-Awareness involves being aware of the various aspects of self-involvement that include traits, behaviors, and feelings. In fact, it is a state of mind where the focus is on yourself. Humans are born with a perfectly sound mind. However, research has also found that infants have a basic sense of self-worth. An example of self-awareness is your ability to share your beliefs with others. It helps us become better decision-makers It gives us more confidence.

Self-Awareness is the ability to tune in to your feelings, thoughts, and actions. Being self-aware also means being able to recognize how other people see you. People who are self-aware recognize their strengths and their challenges.

EMPATHY

DESCRIPTION


Empathy is the ability to empathize with other people's feelings, to see things from their point of view, and to imagine yourself in their place. is a powerful concern for the well-being and happiness of others. There are several types of empathy a person may experience:

Affected Empathy involves the ability to understand another person's feelings and respond appropriately.

Somatic sensitivity involves having some form of physical response to responding to another person's experience. People sometimes feel what someone else is feeling.

Cognitive Empathy involves being able to understand another person's state of mind and what they can think of in response to a situation.

CRITICAL THINKING

DESCRIPTION


Critical Thinking is when the information is collected in the form of any experience or view and is used to analyze, use or evaluate the information collected it is called critical thinking. There are four main aspects to analytical thinking; self-discipline, self-control, and self-discipline.

There are 7 steps that help to improve the process of deep thinking.

  • Identify the problem
  • Gather the details
  • Check the details
  • Make a decision based on the accuracy of the information
  • Measure
  • Perform the analysis
  • Describe your analysis.

    • DECISION MAKING

    DESCRIPTION


    Decision Making is the process in which one has to make a rational and explainable choice out of more than one option. The term decision making is also referred to as a cognitive process. There are three types of decision making Strategic decision where upper-level management of the organization makes long-term decisions that set the direction for an entire organization. decision where decisions regarding how things will be done are taken. Operational decision where day-to-day decisions are made by the lower-level employees to run the operations of the organization smoothly.

    PROBLEM SOLVING

    DESCRIPTION


    Problem Solving is the process of finding a solution to issues that are critical and needs to be worked on urgently also requires attention. If a particular person has the ability to cope up with any difficult situation, then that person is said to have problem-solving skills. Problem-solving is considered one of the most valuable skills and organizations consider this skill while hiring an employee. These are the steps for problem-solving:

  • Identify the problem
  • The reason behind the occurrence of the problem
  • List all the solutions possible for solving that problem
  • Choose the best fit
  • Implement the solution
  • Evaluation of results

    • TIME MANAGEMENT

    DESCRIPTION


    Time Management : In order to increase productivity through efficiency and effectiveness, deliberate efforts are made to exercise control of time spent on the activities because it helps bring more discipline and balance in life. While practicing time management focus is the main key. There are 7 ways for better time management:

  • Focus should be clear.
  • Prepare a task list that you need to complete.
  • Put first things first.
  • Procrastination should be dealt strictly.
  • Focus on one task at a time (stop multitasking).
  • eview and compare your completed tasks with the check list.

    • CREATIVE THINKING

    DESCRIPTION


    Creative Thinking is the process of using soft skills and thinking out of the box to solve a problem or deal with a difficult situation is called creative thinking. Brainstorming dramatically helps with creative thinking and eventually, a unique solution to the problem appears.

    COMMUNICATION

    DESCRIPTION


    Communication is the process where information is transferred through speaking, audio-visuals or writing is called communication It serves as a fundamental tool for learning for humans because the idea, different views, and information is shared and exchanged effectively through communication. There are four types of communication:

  • Passive
  • Aggressive
  • Passive-Aggressive
  • Assertive

    • INTERPERSONAL RELATIONSHIP

    DESCRIPTION


    Interpersonal Relationship is behavioral skills are the methods and techniques a person uses to communicate effectively with others. In a business setting, the term refers to an employee's ability to get along well with others. Social skills begin in communication and listening to attitude and deportation.

    COPING WITH STRESS

    DESCRIPTION


    Coping With Stress is a buzzword that you may have heard recently? If you do a quick search on Pinterest, you will find hundreds of pins about coping skills… all from Coping Skills Bingo to create your Wheel of Coping Skills. Blogs and articles like these can provide useful tips on how to use problem-solving skills, but they don't always provide some very important background information… things like coping skills, and why you use coping skills? So, this article is my own personal attempt to answer similar questions!

    EMOTIONAL INTELLIGENCE

    DESCRIPTION


    Emotional Intelligence is (also known as an emotional quotient or EQ) is the ability to understand, use, and manage your emotions in effective ways to relieve stress, communicate effectively, empathize with others, overcome challenges and resolve conflicts. Emotional intelligence helps you to build strong relationships, succeed in school and work, and achieve your career goals and goals. It can also help you to communicate your feelings, turn purpose into action, and make informed decisions about what is most important to you.
